webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) In 1745 the work began to expand the medieval church building of the parish in Vist. The new church received a very lavish interior. The costs could be shared by no fewer one three sellers in the parish who, in return, had the patronate court alternated among themselves. The inconspicuous roof of the church was painted by Sven Gustavsson Stoltz of Vadstena. The organ was donated by Countess Anna-Maria Lewenhaupt at Bjärka Säby, built by Jonas Wistenius in Lköpping in 1747. The reader closest to the left was completed for the holders at Sturefors - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000568. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419883. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
